1
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:35,660
Winter Begonia

2
00:01:35,660 --> 00:01:37,979
Episode 13

3
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:41,200
(Contract)

4
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:41,620
I’ve persuaded those senior performers
(Contract)

5
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:43,509
I’ve persuaded those senior performers

6
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,320
of Shuiyun Theater into coming to us.

7
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:48,220
Also, I got some information

8
00:01:48,229 --> 00:01:50,610
about Shang Xirui’s new play.

9
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,480
You lad

10
00:02:02,490 --> 00:02:04,170
did something right finally.

11
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,210
It’s unlucky of that prat.

12
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:12,550
He made a contract

13
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:14,680
with Cheng Fengtai.

14
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,150
But he hurt himself by what he did.

15
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:17,820
Yes.

16
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:20,370
Without those performers,

17
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,940
he can’t give a complete show.

18
00:02:22,950 --> 00:02:25,210
How will he perform his new play?

19
00:02:31,079 --> 00:02:31,579
Dad.

20
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:32,940
How do we deal with them?

21
00:02:32,940 --> 00:02:35,420
(Contract)
How do we deal with them?

22
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,210
Ask them to sign an indenture to sell themselves to us.

23
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,300
Once they sign it,

24
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:43,329
we’ll reward them handsomely.

25
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,860
What if they don’t sign?

26
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,100
They don’t?

27
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:54,250
Then never let them to play the leading roles.

28
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:57,150
They must be ashamed to go back after all.

29
00:03:00,730 --> 00:03:03,170
Dad, how wise you are.

30
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:06,110
The Prime Minister, the general and the queen.

31
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,750
Leader, those who left

32
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:10,030
were these important roles.

33
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:11,220
What will we do?

34
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,730
We shouldn’t have let them go.

35
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,200
Before the competition,

36
00:03:17,540 --> 00:03:20,260
they put us in dilemma.

37
00:03:21,510 --> 00:03:22,840
This is regulated in our contract.

38
00:03:23,570 --> 00:03:26,100
Let them go once they pay the penal sum.

39
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,270
I always keep my promise.

40
00:03:28,810 --> 00:03:29,610
Leader.

41
00:03:30,070 --> 00:03:32,850
It’s not right to make the contract.

42
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,150
Leader, you are too stubborn.

43
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,820
Nothing can be changed?

44
00:03:36,829 --> 00:03:38,570
Why are you so

45
00:03:38,579 --> 00:03:39,270
inflexible?

46
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,450
Cut your crap!

47
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:41,390
Our performers are not enough now.

48
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,420
Why don’t you go to borrow some?

49
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:44,620
OK, I’m blamed at the end.

50
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:50,260
Leader. Leader. Leader.

51
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,010
Well,

52
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:08,250
elite.

53
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,410
Come here.

54
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:13,950
Fengtai.

55
00:04:14,390 --> 00:04:16,250
It sounds like satire.

56
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,110
Coward.

57
00:04:19,649 --> 00:04:21,360
You can’t bear my compliment?

58
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:23,390
Have a seat.

59
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:25,810
I found you a job to make the most

60
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:28,000
of what you learned in the university.

61
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,630
I don’t think it’s a good job.

62
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,840
But Fengtai, you can tell me.

63
00:04:36,050 --> 00:04:39,450
Mr. Lei has finished the sketch design of Cave Liuxian.

64
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,530
I also made all the materials ready.

65
00:04:43,030 --> 00:04:44,520
Go back to prepare for it.

66
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:47,180
Go to supervise this project for Mr. Lei.

67
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,200
Me?

68
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:53,360
I am the manager of a theater.

69
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:54,970
It’s winter

70
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,730
with wind and snow.

71
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,610
Do you want me to eat sands there?

72
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:01,690
Fengtai, I’d rather die.

73
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:03,910
It’s even harder than finding a theater.

74
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,850
Then, go to die.

75
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:08,460
Fengtai, this...

76
00:05:09,190 --> 00:05:11,010
Many theaters are in Peking,

77
00:05:11,020 --> 00:05:12,810
but you haven’t found one for me.

78
00:05:13,470 --> 00:05:14,810
I’m also confused.

79
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,860
There are many theaters.

80
00:05:16,870 --> 00:05:18,140
But none of them are sold to us.

81
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,610
If they are not satisfied with too many requests,

82
00:05:20,890 --> 00:05:23,130
simplify the items.

83
00:05:23,140 --> 00:05:24,700
Fengtai, well...

84
00:05:24,710 --> 00:05:26,370
We are still in the first stage.

85
00:05:26,380 --> 00:05:28,610
Once I stepped in their theaters, I was driven out.

86
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:31,730
Also,

87
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:34,060
Mr. Shang and you have fallen out.

88
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,980
So what’s the use of my efforts?

89
00:05:35,990 --> 00:05:37,610
Who told you that we’ve fallen out?

90
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:39,340
He’s silly.

91
00:05:39,350 --> 00:05:40,890
How can I be like him?

92
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,200
You are still friends?

93
00:05:45,610 --> 00:05:46,210
Fengtai,

94
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,130
if so,

95
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:51,690
can I tell you something?

96
00:05:54,140 --> 00:05:55,500
It’s only been several days.

97
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,690
Did he offend someone again?

98
00:05:58,640 --> 00:05:59,490
Something like that.

99
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,620
OK.

100
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:15,840
Got it.

101
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:18,050
Let’s change our duty for a while.

102
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:21,650
I’ll take care of Shuiyun Theater.

103
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:24,240
And you make sure that

104
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,290
Cave Liuxian is founded well.

105
00:06:27,070 --> 00:06:29,490
When you finish, you’ll be rewarded handsomely.

106
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,400
But if you fail...

107
00:06:31,410 --> 00:06:33,010
If I fail, I won’t go back.

108
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,280
Just let me die outside.

109
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:36,370
If you say so,

110
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:38,800
it’s not bad that you fail.

111
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:41,690
Your sister and I will be worriless in the future.

112
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,060
Mr. Shang, I don’t mean to offend,

113
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:48,590
but I advise that you stop asking.

114
00:06:48,810 --> 00:06:50,180
Which troupe

115
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:51,490
in Peking dares

116
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:54,770
help you against Jiang Rongshou?

117
00:06:55,110 --> 00:06:57,290
No matter who will win,

118
00:06:57,520 --> 00:07:00,050
they will be bullied by Jiang.

119
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:03,250
Thanks for your advice.

120
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:05,850
You are right.

121
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:07,250
In my opinion,

122
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,250
it’s best to beg Mr. Jiang.

123
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:10,780
No matter what,

124
00:07:10,790 --> 00:07:13,210
he’s a peer of your father,

125
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,590
so he won’t be too ruthless

126
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:18,220
and make you stop performing for a year.

127
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:21,050
Thank you.

128
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,530
Mr. Shang.

129
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:26,240
Warm buns!

130
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:28,590
Buns!

131
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,020
Tomatoes on sticks!

132
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,730
Tomatoes on sticks!

133
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,730
Tomatoes on sticks!

134
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,000
It’s fine. Leader will be back.

135
00:07:43,010 --> 00:07:43,900
What are we eating?

136
00:07:43,909 --> 00:07:45,340
Yes.

137
00:07:47,030 --> 00:07:49,210
Leader. Leader.

138
00:07:52,650 --> 00:07:53,440
What are you doing?

139
00:07:54,380 --> 00:07:55,530
Are you lazy?

140
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,260
Who told you to stop practicing?

141
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:58,550
Do we need to practice?

142
00:07:58,830 --> 00:08:00,980
We don’t even have enough performers.

143
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:01,980
Right.

144
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:03,700
Leader, if you lose this time,

145
00:08:03,710 --> 00:08:05,110
you can’t perform for a year.

146
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:07,730
Who will be the leading light of Shuiyun Theater?

147
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:09,490
If you are not such coward,

148
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,540
I don’t need to beg others!

149
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,510
Go to practice!

150
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,470
If no one helps us,

151
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:17,140
all of you must step on the stage,

152
00:08:17,150 --> 00:08:19,150
regardless your qualification and the roles you play now!

153
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:20,810
Leader, this...

154
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,410
How can we make it?

155
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,250
Go to practice! Do you want to get punishment?

156
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,300
OK. Practice.

157
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:30,930
Hurry up.

158
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:40,380
Why did you say such words just now?

159
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,789
It’s lucky already

160
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,860
if they perform their roles well.

161
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:45,120
What else can they play?

162
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,050
Do I have another choice?

163
00:08:48,970 --> 00:08:50,640
I didn’t succeed the rules

164
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:51,650
made by father well.

165
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,130
Our staff stole my money.

166
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:55,770
I also make Mr. Cheng’s

167
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:56,850
new rules failed.

168
00:08:57,260 --> 00:08:58,570
I couldn’t stay our men.

169
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,250
What’s worse, they betrayed me.

170
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:02,170
How come you still talk about him?

171
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:03,870
You drove him away.

172
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:05,170
So don’t mention this name.

173
00:09:05,810 --> 00:09:07,360
We had rules.

174
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,850
But no one

175
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:10,450
took them seriously.

176
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:13,610
All in all, people are of different minds.

177
00:09:15,190 --> 00:09:16,810
Minds!

178
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:49,250
Leader, say something.

179
00:09:49,970 --> 00:09:51,450
What should we do?

180
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:52,340
Mr. Shang.

181
00:09:53,570 --> 00:09:56,050
Mr. Shang. Mr. Shang.

182
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,830
Good news. Guess it.

183
00:09:59,070 --> 00:10:00,480
Since we advertised Zhao Feiyan,

184
00:10:00,490 --> 00:10:02,240
I’ve kept receiving calls.

185
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:05,060
Half of the tickets were sold.

186
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:06,970
I am sure

187
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:08,170
that you’ll win.

188
00:10:09,620 --> 00:10:11,150
What a shame.

189
00:10:12,090 --> 00:10:13,130
What did you say?

190
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,010
He said “thanks for our wish”.

191
00:10:16,020 --> 00:10:17,410
Go back to your work.

192
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,160
Shijiu, your words are sweet.

193
00:10:19,370 --> 00:10:21,100
Mr. Shang, I’ll be waiting for you outside.

194
00:10:21,110 --> 00:10:22,370
Take it easy.

195
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:34,570
Leader.

196
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,040
Leader.

197
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,680
Go to apologize to Mr. Cheng, please.

198
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,220
He experienced a lot,

199
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:43,800
so he must have more ways.

200
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:45,010
He’ll help us.

201
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:48,570
Please beg him.

202
00:10:48,580 --> 00:10:50,750
Shuiyun Theater is also his business.

203
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:52,640
He won’t just wait to see us fail.

204
00:10:52,650 --> 00:10:53,120
He has nothing

205
00:10:53,130 --> 00:10:54,270
except money.

206
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,570
Can a businessman help us on opera?

207
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:57,920
Focus on your duty.

208
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,570
Shijiu.

209
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,790
The Cheng’s shamed

210
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,890
our leader with harsh words.

211
00:11:04,980 --> 00:11:07,970
This God of Wealth is way out of our league.

212
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:14,510
What’s going on?

213
00:11:40,810 --> 00:11:43,970
Mr. Cheng. Mr. Cheng. Mr. Cheng.

214
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:01,370
Mr. Cheng.

215
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:02,730
Mr. Shang,

216
00:12:04,290 --> 00:12:06,330
I just employed those performers.

217
00:12:06,740 --> 00:12:09,890
They’ll perform in our Shuiyun Theater.

218
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,770
I don’t know opera well.

219
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:15,970
So it still needs to be approved by you.

220
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,150
Mr. Wang.

221
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:25,370
Mr. Shang.

222
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,890
Mr. Zhu, Mr. Ding.

223
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:31,730
Of course I approve it.

224
00:12:32,430 --> 00:12:33,640
They are good performers

225
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:34,930
in Peking.

226
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:37,500
It’s our honor to have them.

227
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:40,290
I’m really grateful that you join us.

228
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,530
Shuiyun gets a new lease of life.

229
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:43,670
Mr. Shang,

230
00:12:44,210 --> 00:12:45,450
I found performers for you.

231
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,890
As to the opera,

232
00:12:48,210 --> 00:12:48,860
it’s your turn.

233
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,420
I can’t help with it.

234
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,000
Mr. Cheng.

235
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:55,870
Take care, Mr. Cheng.

236
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,220
Why didn’t you say something good to him?

237
00:12:59,230 --> 00:13:00,070
He came to help us

238
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,450
on such a big thing.

239
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,110
I...

240
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,000
I don’t know what to say.

241
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:16,190
Sirs, please come in.

242
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:17,670
After you.

243
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,740
Mr. Cheng.	 Mr. Cheng.

244
00:13:27,820 --> 00:13:29,680
Mr. Cheng. Mr. Cheng. Mr. Cheng.

245
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,390
Mr. Cheng.

246
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:35,050
I invited an expert

247
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:36,410
to check goods for Shuiyun Theater.

248
00:13:37,090 --> 00:13:39,020
Mr. Ma, nice to meet you.

249
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:41,540
Sir, please have a look.

250
00:13:57,350 --> 00:13:58,250
-Mr. Cheng.
-Yes.

251
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,750
Those goods were sent last night.

252
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,670
I saw the truck loading.

253
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:13,370
Amazing.

254
00:14:13,950 --> 00:14:16,740
How exquisite the workmanship is.

255
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:21,310
And the cloth is the best.

256
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:24,080
Sir, good eye.

257
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,970
The best embroiderer in Suzhou made it.

258
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:27,960
Our boss

259
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:30,490
chose the cloth himself.

260
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:32,370
He really puts a lot of efforts.

261
00:14:33,430 --> 00:14:34,510
It’s no wonder.

262
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:36,720
It’s not worse than

263
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,340
what the queen and concubines wear.

264
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,090
Making a new play needs everything from the start.

265
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,190
There’s no reference.

266
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,410
It requests a lot of contributions.

267
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,120
If you see

268
00:14:47,130 --> 00:14:48,170
how Mr. Shang practices,

269
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:50,490
you’ll know what “contributions” mean.

270
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:52,810
I don’t know other things well,

271
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:54,910
but I know that

272
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:57,090
we can’t make any mistake on costumes.

273
00:14:57,330 --> 00:14:58,490
Mr. Cheng. Don’t worry.

274
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,290
I fixed my eyes on

275
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:01,930
the costumes for Shuiyun.

276
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,570
Look, our boss treats others better.

277
00:15:06,770 --> 00:15:07,580
Gosh.

278
00:15:08,090 --> 00:15:09,770
He’s more careful than Mr. Shang.

279
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:11,850
That troupe

280
00:15:12,110 --> 00:15:14,200
is more important than us to him.

281
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:16,760
Shuiyun Theater is ranked No.1.

282
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:19,010
Mr. Shang, how are you?

283
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:21,850
Mr. Shang.

284
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:22,980
Mr. Shang.

285
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:24,310
This is for you.

286
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:27,820
What does this mean?

287
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,100
What information did you get?

288
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:40,570
Sir, our men who came back said

289
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,200
that their leader has a stutter.

290
00:15:42,890 --> 00:15:44,850
He must be Second Chief Gu of Laozi Ridge.

291
00:15:47,770 --> 00:15:49,770
I also think so.

292
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:52,630
He seems to be a coward.

293
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:54,180
But in fact, he’s ambitious.

294
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:57,170
He broke the rules.

295
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:01,160
Seems that he doesn’t agree with his chief.

296
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,910
Yes, he robbed twice for a month.

297
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,150
It’s unusual.

298
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:08,320
Sir, how about asking our men

299
00:16:08,330 --> 00:16:10,100
to rob the goods back?

300
00:16:10,110 --> 00:16:11,210
They are bandits.

301
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:12,700
How can our men

302
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:14,090
get them back from bandits?

303
00:16:15,510 --> 00:16:16,730
So you mean...

304
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,560
Since he wants the goods,

305
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:28,080
I’ll send him some.

306
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,080
Look, second chief.

307
00:16:32,290 --> 00:16:33,890
Our bros got some new goods.

308
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,290
Look. Wine.

309
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,390
Made by Zheng Company.

310
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:38,970
Did you drink that?

311
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,470
Look, he’s also the chairman

312
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:43,010
of Peking Chamber of Commerce.

313
00:16:44,010 --> 00:16:45,510
Good things.

314
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:46,320
Good.

315
00:16:46,950 --> 00:16:48,480
Check them.

316
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:51,110
When we gain rich harvest,

317
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,940
we need to stop

318
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:56,010
in case our chief has troubles.

319
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:56,550
Yes. Yes.

320
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,030
Bro.

321
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:57,560
Hurry.

322
00:16:58,890 --> 00:17:00,290
Chief. Chief.

323
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:03,130
What troubles the chief brought to you?

324
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:05,119
Chief, why are you back?

325
00:17:05,130 --> 00:17:06,569
How dare you ask me?

326
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:08,170
If I come back one day later,

327
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:11,069
this hill will be left nothing.

328
00:17:11,079 --> 00:17:12,550
No, chief.

329
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:13,650
Do not misunderstand me.

330
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:14,829
How dare I?

331
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,849
To celebrate the New Year,

332
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:19,190
I took some gifts for our bros,

333
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,020
which brings them more fortune.

334
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,609
What the heck of the fortune?

335
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,829
I made the rule.

336
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:32,210
Don’t rob one company twice in a month.

337
00:17:32,970 --> 00:17:33,950
Yeah.

338
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,730
You just ignore me?

339
00:17:35,740 --> 00:17:37,070
They sent these to us.

340
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,280
We didn’t rob.

341
00:17:43,670 --> 00:17:46,080
You are too ambitious these days!

342
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:50,250
Stay here

343
00:17:50,660 --> 00:17:52,170
to catch rabbits!

344
00:17:52,450 --> 00:17:53,410
Catch rabbits?

345
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:54,990
It’s still in the New Year.

346
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,130
-Go!
-Chief.

347
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:03,820
Second chief.

348
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,940
Will we see the goods?

349
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:08,010
Cut the crap!

350
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:11,330
Can’t you see that I’m annoyed?

351
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,370
Here’s a letter.

352
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:16,970
Read it.

353
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:19,730
Are you out of breath?

354
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:21,120
Hurry up.

355
00:18:21,130 --> 00:18:21,900
Yeah. Yeah.

356
00:18:22,620 --> 00:18:23,110
Here.

357
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,440
Read it.

358
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:28,930
What’s in it?

359
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:30,030
Who knows?

360
00:18:30,420 --> 00:18:33,530
Chairman Zheng of Peking Chamber of Commerce.

361
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:47,290
Interesting.

362
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,630
What’s this?

363
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:07,270
Smell of garlic!

364
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:11,390
Mr. Shang sent some fried sausage.

365
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:13,870
Why didn’t he ask me

366
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,610
whether I love it?

367
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:18,830
Mr. Shang

368
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,530
sends different kinds of food every day.

369
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:22,030
There must be something

370
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,280
that you like.

371
00:19:26,050 --> 00:19:27,690
How childish he is.

372
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:39,080
let’s talk something serious.

373
00:19:40,340 --> 00:19:42,330
The chamber of commerce

374
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:43,640
doesn’t make money

375
00:19:43,650 --> 00:19:45,130
but brings a lot of troubles to me.

376
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:48,050
They keep bothering me.

377
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:50,190
How will they celebrate the New Year?

378
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:54,070
They can’t

379
00:19:54,980 --> 00:19:56,570
make money these days.

380
00:19:58,220 --> 00:19:59,130
For the two months,

381
00:19:59,810 --> 00:20:01,560
once they passed Laozi Ridge,

382
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:02,440
they were robbed.

383
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:04,900
Seeing everything go well with us,

384
00:20:05,130 --> 00:20:06,770
of course they are jealous.

385
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:10,410
So they want to go through our road.

386
00:20:12,450 --> 00:20:15,140
Laozi Ridge. Chief Gu.

387
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,420
Whether Chief Gu robs

388
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,210
depends on his mood.

389
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:23,190
The chamber is too unlucky.

390
00:20:23,340 --> 00:20:24,560
It makes sense.

391
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:27,030
But Laozi Ridge robbed

392
00:20:27,170 --> 00:20:29,170
more frequently than before.

393
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,010
They almost robbed everything of the passers.

394
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:33,730
I think

395
00:20:34,990 --> 00:20:36,930
there must be something.

396
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:40,400
This is not Chief Gu’s style.

397
00:20:41,270 --> 00:20:42,770
The robberies are too many.

398
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:45,750
Who dares go through Laozi Ridge in future?

399
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,370
It’s like killing the hen for eggs.

400
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:49,820
He’s not so stupid.

401
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:58,420
The second chief did it.

402
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,440
I also think it’s him.

403
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:06,300
It’s the end of the year.

404
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:08,330
Bring gifts to Laozi Ridge

405
00:21:09,070 --> 00:21:10,450
to get some information.

406
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:13,590
Mr. Cheng. Don’t worry.

407
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:51,570
Excuse me. Excuse me.

408
00:21:58,690 --> 00:21:59,640
Have it when it’s still warm.

409
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:03,950
Mr. Shang.

410
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:06,430
Did you give me a live charcoal?

411
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,410
No.

412
00:22:07,870 --> 00:22:10,080
I forgot that people from Shanghai don’t like garlic.

413
00:22:10,580 --> 00:22:12,690
So I bought you a toasted sweet potato.

414
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,530
I didn’t know my wife embarrassed you.

415
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:41,840
Her words were harsh.

416
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,530
I’m sorry for that.

417
00:22:45,190 --> 00:22:45,970
No.

418
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:49,080
I’m not afraid of her harsh words.

419
00:22:49,830 --> 00:22:51,410
I’ d rather scolded by her every day

420
00:22:52,690 --> 00:22:54,580
than be aloof from you.

421
00:22:57,950 --> 00:22:59,810
Can I enter Shuiyun Theater again?

422
00:23:01,090 --> 00:23:02,130
It’s my pleasure.

423
00:23:05,910 --> 00:23:08,050
So don’t use honorifics with me anymore.

424
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:11,290
It sounds aloof.

425
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,330
My elder sister

426
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:28,490
adopted a cat.

427
00:23:29,930 --> 00:23:31,490
This cat always

428
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:33,870
put a mouse

429
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:34,960
in front of her room.

430
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:37,420
And after all the surrounding mice were caught,

431
00:23:37,430 --> 00:23:38,950
it sent her geckos.

432
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:43,250
Every time, my sister was scared to death.

433
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:45,310
This cat is capable.

434
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:51,120
You compare me to a cat?

435
00:24:01,430 --> 00:24:03,290
OK, stop eating this.

436
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:05,010
I’ll take you to have something good.

437
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:16,070
Excuse me.

438
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:24,950
Mrs. Cheng.

439
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:26,970
I called the freight agent.

440
00:24:27,190 --> 00:24:29,920
A performer of Shuiyun came there.

441
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,390
Mr. Cheng and he went out together.

442
00:24:34,910 --> 00:24:37,850
I heard that Shuiyun Theater will have a competition.

443
00:24:38,490 --> 00:24:39,940
I also heard it.

444
00:24:40,070 --> 00:24:42,400
Almost everyone in Peking has known it.

445
00:24:42,660 --> 00:24:44,400
Mr. Cheng might be called to help.

446
00:24:48,090 --> 00:24:49,260
Is he bewitched?

447
00:24:50,140 --> 00:24:52,480
He really takes that troupe

448
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:54,330
as his business?

449
00:25:06,080 --> 00:25:08,210
I’ve made your costumes ready,

450
00:25:08,670 --> 00:25:10,410
and invited enough performers.

451
00:25:10,830 --> 00:25:12,370
I’m not good at opera.

452
00:25:12,910 --> 00:25:14,230
So it’s your show time.

453
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,430
Mr. Cheng, just wait for my show.

454
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:19,070
See you.

455
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:16,210
Alright.

456
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:17,970
Time’s up.

457
00:26:19,370 --> 00:26:21,670
Female roles walk on the ice.

458
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:24,040
Male roles also step on the ice

459
00:26:24,050 --> 00:26:25,650
with this posture.

460
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:28,570
It’s not finished?

461
00:26:28,870 --> 00:26:30,620
You don’t want to go down?

462
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:45,580
Stand up!

463
00:26:57,250 --> 00:26:58,570
Don’t play a chimney.

464
00:26:59,370 --> 00:27:00,570
Have you do well on this posture?

465
00:27:01,840 --> 00:27:03,570
Leader. My feet are numb.

466
00:27:03,850 --> 00:27:04,810
I can’t stand.

467
00:27:05,050 --> 00:27:06,490
Come to have a rest.

468
00:27:07,340 --> 00:27:08,520
Where is numb?

469
00:27:09,390 --> 00:27:10,170
Show me.

470
00:27:10,290 --> 00:27:10,710
Here.

471
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:11,590
Here? Come.

472
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:16,980
No... It’s not numb, leader!

473
00:27:16,990 --> 00:27:17,990
It’s not numb.

474
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,190
-It’s not numb?
-No.

475
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:19,890
No.

476
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:24,590
Whose feet are numb? Tell me.

477
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:26,210
I’ll help to relieve your discomfort.

478
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:35,290
Take small steps.

479
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:39,850
Mr. Cheng.

480
00:27:40,140 --> 00:27:40,720
Mr. Cheng.

481
00:27:41,010 --> 00:27:41,410
Mr. Cheng.

482
00:27:41,420 --> 00:27:42,890
Mr. Cheng. Watch the ice.

483
00:27:44,190 --> 00:27:45,050
Mr. Cheng. Take care.

484
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,530
Mr. Shang. Are you butchering pigs?

485
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:55,180
Too much ice is on the ground.

486
00:27:55,370 --> 00:27:56,720
This helps them to practice figure.

487
00:27:57,940 --> 00:27:58,750
Leader, I…

488
00:27:58,760 --> 00:27:59,570
Stand up.

489
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:01,130
Stand up!

490
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,930
Rome was not built in a day.

491
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:09,150
It won’t work even though you force them.

492
00:28:10,050 --> 00:28:10,850
Also,

493
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,290
you torture them in this way.

494
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:15,050
But can you do it well?

495
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:17,910
Mr. Cheng, you look down on me.

496
00:28:18,310 --> 00:28:19,360
I don’t dare.

497
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:22,680
Leader. How about doing it for us?

498
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:24,220
Yes, leader.

499
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:25,970
Please show us.

500
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:27,610
Let us have a look.

501
00:28:55,790 --> 00:28:56,460
Look carefully.

502
00:28:57,430 --> 00:28:59,230
The key of stepping on it

503
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:01,430
is stabilizing your lower body.

504
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:05,380
Make every step stable.

505
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:07,910
Don’t be afraid of falling down.

506
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:10,210
Don’t make fear defeat you.

507
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:22,300
Bravo!

508
00:29:22,310 --> 00:29:23,070
Amazing!

509
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:25,070
Bravo! Bravo!

510
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:26,070
Our leader is wonderful.

511
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:26,690
Yes.

512
00:29:32,350 --> 00:29:35,250
Bravo! Bravo! Bravo!

513
00:29:39,260 --> 00:29:41,160
Bravo! Bravo! Bravo!

514
00:29:46,070 --> 00:29:48,170
Bravo! Bravo! Bravo!

515
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:49,240
Unbelievable!

516
00:29:49,670 --> 00:29:50,270
Bravo!

517
00:29:50,280 --> 00:29:51,320
You are so steady.

518
00:30:01,030 --> 00:30:02,280
Leader. Take it.

519
00:30:09,150 --> 00:30:12,740
Bravo! Bravo! Bravo!

520
00:30:20,190 --> 00:30:21,520
Waiter! My noodles!

521
00:30:21,530 --> 00:30:22,390
Give me a second.

522
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:24,570
Here are your noodles.

523
00:30:26,180 --> 00:30:27,060
Sorry to make you wait.

524
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:28,580
Sorry.

525
00:30:30,140 --> 00:30:30,790
Here.

526
00:30:44,580 --> 00:30:46,090
I treated you to roast duck,

527
00:30:46,750 --> 00:30:48,110
but you treat in here?

528
00:30:48,620 --> 00:30:49,850
I took you here

529
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:51,400
to let you taste...

530
00:30:51,670 --> 00:30:52,690
I’m sorry.

531
00:30:54,450 --> 00:30:55,650
To let you taste the good food

532
00:30:55,660 --> 00:30:57,250
that I’ve liked for years.

533
00:30:57,260 --> 00:30:58,220
It really tastes delicious.

534
00:30:58,230 --> 00:30:59,830
It can’t be run for 40 years if it’s not good.

535
00:31:01,340 --> 00:31:03,670
Mr. Shang. Mr. Shang.

536
00:31:04,100 --> 00:31:05,640
Come in, please.

537
00:31:06,110 --> 00:31:08,120
Have a seat.

538
00:31:10,870 --> 00:31:11,350
Have a seat.

539
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,930
Mr. Shang, it’s been a long time.

540
00:31:14,940 --> 00:31:16,440
You must be busy with your new play.

541
00:31:17,410 --> 00:31:18,770
This sir doesn’t look familiar.

542
00:31:19,590 --> 00:31:20,620
What would you like to eat?

543
00:31:20,630 --> 00:31:21,900
What would you like, Mr. Cheng?

544
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:23,800
I’m not hungry.

545
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:26,770
We are already here. Have a taste.

546
00:31:26,910 --> 00:31:28,590
As usual, two portions.

547
00:31:29,210 --> 00:31:30,580
No need to change.

548
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:31,200
Thanks.

549
00:31:31,620 --> 00:31:32,470
Lower your voice.

550
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:33,650
Two portions of meat sauce noodles.

551
00:31:33,660 --> 00:31:35,250
Mr. Shang rewarded us with two cents!

552
00:31:35,260 --> 00:31:37,630
Mr. Shang rewarded us with two cents!

553
00:31:42,250 --> 00:31:43,900
The oil for 40 years.

554
00:31:45,310 --> 00:31:47,530
You don’t need to lick the table.

555
00:32:12,610 --> 00:32:13,290
Enjoy.

556
00:32:18,820 --> 00:32:19,530
What are you looking at?

557
00:32:24,030 --> 00:32:26,610
I wondered why I heard the sound of a lucky bird.

558
00:32:27,050 --> 00:32:28,360
Look who is here.

559
00:32:30,110 --> 00:32:31,190
Who is here?

560
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,230
Hurry. Hurry.

561
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:33,850
Come to see.

562
00:32:34,430 --> 00:32:35,840
Mr. Shang.

563
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:37,620
It’s really Mr. Shang.

564
00:32:37,630 --> 00:32:39,210
Mr. Shang. Mr. Shang.

565
00:32:41,630 --> 00:32:43,050
Mr. Shang is here.

566
00:32:43,270 --> 00:32:44,240
Mr. Shang.

567
00:32:44,430 --> 00:32:45,060
Nice to meet you.

568
00:32:45,070 --> 00:32:46,460
Nice to meet you.

569
00:32:46,470 --> 00:32:48,840
Mr. Shang. I like your opera best,

570
00:32:49,390 --> 00:32:50,960
especially that...

571
00:32:51,510 --> 00:32:53,950
Yang Paifeng.

572
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,220
Yes, yes.

573
00:32:55,230 --> 00:32:56,440
I tell you.

574
00:32:56,650 --> 00:32:59,920
I like the matchmaker played by you best.

575
00:33:00,220 --> 00:33:01,180
Let me recall how to sing.

576
00:33:02,140 --> 00:33:04,660
Mr. Shang, can I show it to you?

577
00:33:05,550 --> 00:33:06,600
Show it.

578
00:33:07,030 --> 00:33:07,760
Yeah.

579
00:33:08,290 --> 00:33:13,800
My lady

580
00:33:13,810 --> 00:33:23,010
You are so elegant

581
00:33:24,670 --> 00:33:26,850
Mr. Shang. Please excuse me.

582
00:33:26,860 --> 00:33:27,520
Please excuse me.

583
00:33:27,530 --> 00:33:28,770
Well, Mr. Shang.

584
00:33:28,780 --> 00:33:30,600
You also look excited.

585
00:33:30,610 --> 00:33:32,440
Can I show you a part?

586
00:33:34,010 --> 00:33:35,970
OK. Show it.

587
00:33:36,120 --> 00:33:36,980
Excuse me.

588
00:33:36,990 --> 00:33:38,320
Show it.

589
00:33:38,490 --> 00:33:39,560
Only one line.

590
00:33:42,230 --> 00:33:52,600
A man who loses position may be bullied

591
00:33:53,790 --> 00:33:55,150
OK. Stop it.

592
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:57,860
Mr. Shang, how about you sing for us?

593
00:33:57,870 --> 00:33:58,930
Yes, Mr. Shang.

594
00:33:58,940 --> 00:33:59,880
Please sing a part.

595
00:33:59,890 --> 00:34:01,400
Yes.

596
00:34:02,260 --> 00:34:03,810
Mr. Shang, please.

597
00:34:04,940 --> 00:34:06,980
I didn’t come for a long time.

598
00:34:06,990 --> 00:34:08,300
So please

599
00:34:08,310 --> 00:34:09,489
stop it.

600
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:10,570
Everybody.

601
00:34:10,949 --> 00:34:12,190
Mr. Shang didn’t come for long.

602
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:13,400
Just let him enjoy the meal.

603
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:14,750
He graces our restaurant

604
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:16,100
with his presence.

605
00:34:16,750 --> 00:34:18,110
Here. Enjoy your noodles.

606
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:21,370
Mr. Shang, it’s not easy to meet you.

607
00:34:21,989 --> 00:34:23,290
Please sing something.

608
00:34:23,300 --> 00:34:24,870
Sing whatever you like.

609
00:34:25,150 --> 00:34:26,320
We are not picky.

610
00:34:26,330 --> 00:34:27,860
Right, we are not picky.

611
00:34:27,870 --> 00:34:29,040
Please, Mr. Shang.

612
00:34:29,050 --> 00:34:30,560
Please, sing something.

613
00:34:30,889 --> 00:34:32,010
Just several lines.

614
00:34:32,020 --> 00:34:33,030
Please, Mr. Shang.

615
00:34:33,790 --> 00:34:34,530
I don’t!

616
00:34:35,630 --> 00:34:37,330
I’m hungry. I’ll eat noodles.

617
00:34:37,340 --> 00:34:38,580
If you like opera,

618
00:34:38,710 --> 00:34:39,639
watch our performance

619
00:34:39,650 --> 00:34:41,040
in the theater.

620
00:34:41,500 --> 00:34:43,679
You’ll enjoy a complete show.

621
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,570
Then I can make more money.

622
00:34:49,469 --> 00:34:51,980
Mr. Shang, we would like to go to the theater,

623
00:34:52,550 --> 00:34:54,810
but your performances are too few.

624
00:34:54,820 --> 00:34:55,530
Yes.

625
00:34:55,540 --> 00:34:57,590
We all miss you.

626
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,260
Am I right?

627
00:34:58,270 --> 00:34:59,040
Right.

628
00:34:59,050 --> 00:34:59,890
Yes.

629
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:02,320
I’m busy with my new opera.

630
00:35:02,710 --> 00:35:05,520
Hope you watch it in the theater.

631
00:35:05,860 --> 00:35:07,260
Of course.

632
00:35:07,270 --> 00:35:07,880
We will go.

633
00:35:07,890 --> 00:35:10,280
We must support your new opera.

634
00:35:10,430 --> 00:35:10,940
Yes. Yes.

635
00:35:10,950 --> 00:35:11,920
We will go.

636
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:16,950
What will Mr. Chen play in this competition?

637
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,650
It’s...

638
00:35:19,690 --> 00:35:21,540
It’s Yan Xijiao.

639
00:35:21,550 --> 00:35:22,400
Yes.

640
00:35:23,750 --> 00:35:24,950
You are well-informed.

641
00:35:25,990 --> 00:35:27,810
They posted what they’ll perform

642
00:35:27,820 --> 00:35:28,980
on December 9th.

643
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:31,370
Mr. Chen’s Yan Xijiao

644
00:35:31,870 --> 00:35:33,360
is amazing.

645
00:35:33,670 --> 00:35:35,640
Do you know why?

646
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:36,750
Tell us.

647
00:35:36,910 --> 00:35:37,740
Why?

648
00:35:37,750 --> 00:35:39,900
Because

649
00:35:40,080 --> 00:35:42,950
he’ll show Sage’s Footwork.

650
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:44,590
Sage’s Footwork?

651
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:48,310
You didn’t see it,

652
00:35:48,610 --> 00:35:49,920
but you must know it.

653
00:35:50,670 --> 00:35:53,790
Jiang Rongshou performed that for the empress dowager.

654
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:54,980
She loved it

655
00:35:55,310 --> 00:35:57,240
very much

656
00:35:58,070 --> 00:35:59,600
and announced that

657
00:36:00,060 --> 00:36:03,040
Sage’s Footwork could only be shown in the palace.

658
00:36:03,460 --> 00:36:06,390
The public couldn’t watch it.

659
00:36:07,310 --> 00:36:08,420
That’s the story.

660
00:36:08,430 --> 00:36:11,470
Mr. Jiang is grateful to the empress dowager.

661
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:15,630
Now he taught his nephew, Chen Renxiang.

662
00:36:15,910 --> 00:36:17,280
Chen Renxiang?

663
00:36:17,490 --> 00:36:18,730
Mr. Chen.

664
00:36:19,790 --> 00:36:21,560
Mr. Chen is skillful.

665
00:36:21,990 --> 00:36:23,880
But he’s not a member of Jiang.

666
00:36:24,570 --> 00:36:26,470
Can he learn it well?

667
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:30,160
It’s not important.

668
00:36:30,470 --> 00:36:31,360
I tell you.

669
00:36:31,500 --> 00:36:33,630
It’s enough only if he

670
00:36:33,990 --> 00:36:35,510
learns a little. Got it?

671
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:37,160
Reasonable.

672
00:36:37,500 --> 00:36:38,200
I don’t think so.

673
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:40,960
In most cases, the thing you never see

674
00:36:41,380 --> 00:36:44,190
are just gimmicks.

675
00:36:44,610 --> 00:36:45,540
Sir,

676
00:36:45,790 --> 00:36:47,420
you can’t say so.

677
00:36:47,590 --> 00:36:48,820
Do you agree with me?

678
00:36:48,830 --> 00:36:49,440
Yes.

679
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,100
Yes. Yes.

680
00:36:52,110 --> 00:36:54,620
It’s just a kind of footwork.

681
00:36:55,500 --> 00:36:56,120
I also have that.

682
00:36:57,030 --> 00:36:58,350
Just wait for my special skill.

683
00:36:59,200 --> 00:36:59,940
Mr. Shang,

684
00:36:59,950 --> 00:37:01,520
what’s your skill?

685
00:37:01,530 --> 00:37:03,010
Can you show us?

686
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:04,600
Please show us.

687
00:37:05,310 --> 00:37:07,120
To open our horizons.

688
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:08,310
No, I can’t!

689
00:37:08,710 --> 00:37:09,670
If you are curious,

690
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:11,810
go to watch in the theater on December 9th.

691
00:37:12,190 --> 00:37:13,080
What’s the name of it?

692
00:37:16,180 --> 00:37:17,340
What’s the name?

693
00:37:17,550 --> 00:37:21,000
It’s named Fairy’s Footwork.

694
00:37:21,670 --> 00:37:22,920
An interesting name.

695
00:37:23,070 --> 00:37:25,160
Fairy’s Footwork.

696
00:37:28,550 --> 00:37:29,830
Please

697
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,880
advertise it for me.

698
00:37:32,230 --> 00:37:34,800
Tell others that Fairy’s Footwork

699
00:37:34,950 --> 00:37:36,280
is my special skill.

700
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:38,370
Our pioneer would like it if he could see.

701
00:37:38,630 --> 00:37:40,180
See you on December 9th.

702
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:41,300
Don’t miss the only chance!

703
00:37:41,310 --> 00:37:42,140
OK!

704
00:37:42,150 --> 00:37:44,920
-No problem.
-That’s great.

705
00:37:45,190 --> 00:37:46,050
OK, everyone.

706
00:37:46,060 --> 00:37:47,800
Mr. Shang didn’t come for long.

707
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,260
Let us leave him to enjoy the noodles.

708
00:37:49,270 --> 00:37:49,700
OK.

709
00:37:49,710 --> 00:37:50,820
Let’s go back.

710
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:52,440
Mr. Shang, we’ll stop bothering you.

711
00:37:59,710 --> 00:38:00,990
Mr. Cheng, why don’t you eat?

712
00:38:04,270 --> 00:38:05,470
They are all yours.

713
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:23,310
Mr. Ning.

714
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:25,230
Shang Xirui...

715
00:38:27,570 --> 00:38:30,160
Don’t disturb his highness

716
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:34,010
in case he blames you if he loses.

717
00:38:36,710 --> 00:38:38,740
That was melted from snow on Jade Spring Hill.

718
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:41,160
Have a taste.

719
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:43,880
OK.

720
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:50,610
Good tea.

721
00:38:51,930 --> 00:38:53,710
You are absent-minded.

722
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:57,360
Mr. Ning, you know it.

723
00:38:57,500 --> 00:38:58,680
I am a rough guy.

724
00:38:59,070 --> 00:39:00,820
It’s a waste

725
00:39:01,380 --> 00:39:03,120
that you give me something delicate.

726
00:39:03,270 --> 00:39:04,810
Put on an act.

727
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:08,100
You are more and more like

728
00:39:08,110 --> 00:39:10,230
the chairman of the Opera Association.

729
00:39:13,700 --> 00:39:15,960
Jiang is too mean.

730
00:39:16,310 --> 00:39:17,740
He incites the two kids

731
00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:19,160
to fight by all means.

732
00:39:19,460 --> 00:39:22,720
Performers push themselves

733
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:26,360
to make perfect shows,

734
00:39:27,390 --> 00:39:29,840
which is audiences’ luck.

735
00:39:30,300 --> 00:39:31,510
It’s not bad.

736
00:39:33,810 --> 00:39:35,980
You are right.

737
00:39:36,670 --> 00:39:37,740
I heard that

738
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,710
Shang Xirui thought of

739
00:39:40,790 --> 00:39:42,660
Fairy’s Footwork from a painting.

740
00:39:42,670 --> 00:39:43,260
This is his weapon

741
00:39:43,270 --> 00:39:45,040
to fight against Jiang’s Sage’s Footwork.

742
00:39:45,790 --> 00:39:46,950
This kid

743
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:52,090
is not Shang Juzhen’s biological son,

744
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:56,330
but he’s more talented

745
00:39:56,730 --> 00:39:57,620
than Shang Juzhen.

746
00:39:57,960 --> 00:39:59,070
When it comes to painting,

747
00:39:59,460 --> 00:40:02,090
my scripture is missing.

748
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:07,240
Your highness,

749
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,520
that’s a reward from the palace.

750
00:40:09,650 --> 00:40:11,000
You have to find it.

751
00:40:18,570 --> 00:40:19,760
Nice tea.

752
00:40:20,710 --> 00:40:22,480
When will they compete?

753
00:40:22,790 --> 00:40:23,870
December 9th.

754
00:40:24,570 --> 00:40:25,320
December 9th?

755
00:40:28,430 --> 00:40:29,960
A good day.

756
00:40:31,750 --> 00:40:33,440
It was also on December 9th

757
00:40:34,770 --> 00:40:36,230
when we first entered the palace.

758
00:40:38,070 --> 00:40:38,710
I made it.

759
00:40:39,070 --> 00:40:40,840
I won’t lose.

760
00:40:49,070 --> 00:40:54,340
Bravo! Bravo! Bravo!

761
00:40:54,350 --> 00:40:55,380
You also played well.

762
00:40:55,390 --> 00:40:56,940
Every note is correct.

763
00:40:57,130 --> 00:40:58,130
Thanks for your compliment.

764
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:00,430
Here. Leader.

765
00:41:00,440 --> 00:41:01,520
Have some tea.

766
00:41:01,750 --> 00:41:03,040
Mr. Cheng. Have some tea.

767
00:41:03,570 --> 00:41:04,310
Thanks.

768
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,340
Take care.

769
00:41:05,350 --> 00:41:06,770
Handle them gently.

770
00:41:06,990 --> 00:41:07,610
Mr. Du.

771
00:41:07,620 --> 00:41:08,370
Mr. Du. Mr. Du. Mr. Du.

772
00:41:08,380 --> 00:41:10,220
Come in. Come in.

773
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,420
Give us a hand!

774
00:41:11,430 --> 00:41:12,800
My ultimate weapon’s here.

775
00:41:12,810 --> 00:41:14,000
Don’t break them.

776
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:18,330
Take care.

777
00:41:18,830 --> 00:41:21,040
Watch the lights. Lower it.

778
00:41:25,430 --> 00:41:26,850
Take care. Step aside.

779
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:29,280
Take care. Someone’s back.

780
00:41:29,950 --> 00:41:31,020
-Take care.
-Handle it gently.

781
00:41:31,030 --> 00:41:32,450
Take care of the drum head.

782
00:41:32,610 --> 00:41:33,800
Your hands. Your hands.

783
00:41:34,350 --> 00:41:35,060
Thanks. Thanks.

784
00:41:35,070 --> 00:41:36,190
Thanks. Thanks. Thanks.

785
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:37,410
Thanks. Thanks.

786
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:44,520
The drum is so big.

787
00:41:45,200 --> 00:41:46,400
The work is elaborate.

788
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:51,150
The shoe has sponge and leather in it.

789
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:52,730
It’s so soft. Try on.

790
00:41:58,550 --> 00:42:01,710
Go in to recite your lines.

791
00:42:02,110 --> 00:42:03,780
I’ll test you later.

792
00:42:04,060 --> 00:42:05,370
Remember it, or be hit.

793
00:42:06,550 --> 00:42:07,250
OK.

794
00:42:07,260 --> 00:42:07,770
Let’s go.

795
00:42:07,780 --> 00:42:08,200
OK. OK.

796
00:42:08,210 --> 00:42:09,290
Go. Go.

797
00:42:17,870 --> 00:42:18,560
Mr. Cheng.

798
00:42:19,190 --> 00:42:20,040
Go back as well.

799
00:42:23,350 --> 00:42:24,690
I am your investor.

800
00:42:25,310 --> 00:42:26,560
Can’t I watch?

801
00:42:27,450 --> 00:42:28,950
I want to give you a surprise

802
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:30,160
on the stage.

803
00:42:31,780 --> 00:42:32,570
Mr. Cheng.

804
00:42:32,870 --> 00:42:34,700
You’ve been here for a day.

805
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:35,990
You’d better go back,

806
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:38,200
otherwise Mrs. Cheng may come to

807
00:42:38,210 --> 00:42:39,610
find you.

808
00:42:40,230 --> 00:42:41,370
Xiao Lai, mind your words.

809
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:43,300
He doesn’t understand after all.

810
00:42:43,310 --> 00:42:44,960
Yes, he doesn’t understand.

811
00:42:45,910 --> 00:42:48,960
OK. I know.

812
00:42:55,790 --> 00:42:56,420
By the way,

813
00:42:57,300 --> 00:42:59,430
I’ll send you the costumes

814
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:00,400
for Zhao Feiyan in several days.

815
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:01,540
Thanks, Mr. Cheng.

816
00:43:01,550 --> 00:43:03,200
Hurry. Don’t waste time.

817
00:43:11,450 --> 00:43:12,560
Come on. Xirui.

818
00:43:17,590 --> 00:43:18,480
Come on.

819
00:43:19,550 --> 00:43:21,380
After practicing Fairy Footwork,

820
00:43:22,150 --> 00:43:24,530
let’s rehearse the other parts.
